        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 24</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num024-P254v-L21_trl" n="21"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.004.023.trl.xml#Num023-P254v-L21_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="page" n="255r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             Balaam saw that it was good in the eyes of the Lord to bless
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             Israel, and this time he did not go as on other times to meet
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             divinations. And he set his face toward the wilderness.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="2">And Balaam raised his eyes and he saw
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             Israel camping according to its tribes, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             the prophecy of the Lord came on him.</l>
                        <l n="3">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             he took up his parable, and said, ‘Thus says Balaam, son
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             of Beor, and thus says the young man whose eyes are open:</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="4">The one who heard the speeches of God says thus,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             he sees the vision of the mighty God, prophecy falls on him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             and therefore his eyes are open.</l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             How good are your tents, oh Jacob, and your places of dwelling,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             oh Israel!</l>
                        <l n="6">They turn like rivers,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             the Lord has planted them like gardens by a river, like sandalwood
                            trees,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             like cedar trees by the waters.</l>
                        <l n="7">Water will flow
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             from their delicate branches, and his seed is in many waters,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and by that his king will be higher than Agag, and his kingdom will be
                            exalted.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="8">A strong God is he who brought them out from Egypt,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-024-seg001_trl" />he has given him
                                strength<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-024-seg001_trl" /><ref
                                n="1" target="#Num-024-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> like the
                            strength of a rhinoceros. With that power
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             he will consume kingdoms, his enemies, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             he will destroy their bones, and he will cut them with arrows.</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="255v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             He knelt, laid down as a lion, and as a lioness; who
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             will be able to stand him up? Blessed are those who bless you, and
                            cursed are those who curse you.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="10">And Balak’s anger was kindled against Balaam,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             and he struck his hands together. And Balak said to Balaam,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             ‘I took you to curse my enemies, and, lo, you have
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             blessed them these three times.</l>
                        <l n="11">And now
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             flee to your own place. I said, “I would certainly honour
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             you,” but, lo, the Lord has begrudged honour to you.’</l>
                        <l n="12">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             And Balaam said to Balak, ‘Lo, I said also to your envoys
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             whom you sent to me, saying,</l>
                        <l n="13">“Though Balak were to give me
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             his house full of silver and gold, I would not be able to go beyond the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             word of the Lord, to do good or bad of my own heart.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             And only what the Lord speaks: I will speak that.”</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="14">And now, lo, I go to my people. Come,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             I will advise you how to act now, because the deeds
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             that this people will do to you and to your people:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             all that will happen in the latter days.’</l>
                        <l n="15">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             And he took up his parable, and said, ‘Thus says Balaam,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             son of Beor, and thus says the young man whose eyes are open,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="16">The one who heard the speeches of God says thus,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             the one who knows the knowledge of the |most| high God; he
                            <milestone unit="page" n="256r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             sees the vision of the mighty God, prophecy falls on him and therefore
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             his eyes are open.</l>
                        <l n="17">I will see him, but not
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             now. I will view him, but not soon. A star will step
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             from Jacob, and a tribe will rise out of Israel and will cut the edges
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             of Moab and will break down all the sons of Sheth.</l>
                        <l n="18">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             And Edom will perish, and Seir will be a possession
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             for its own enemies, and Israel will do a remarkable thing.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="19">And one from Jacob will rule and will destroy that remains
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             of the city.’</l>
                        <l n="20">And he saw Amalek, and he took up
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             his parable, and said, ‘Amalek was the first of the kingdoms, but his
                            end
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             |arrives| at destruction.’</l>
                        <l n="21">And he saw the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             Kenites and took up his parable, and said, ‘In a strong place is
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             your dwelling place, and you put your nest in a rock.</l>
                        <l n="22">But, indeed,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             Kain will be for destruction, until Asshur shall take
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             you captive.’</l>
                        <l n="23">And he took up his parable, and said,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             ‘Woe, who will live more than the borders that God set him?</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="24">And ships will come from Kittim and will afflict
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             Asshur and will afflict Eber, and he, too, will
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             be for destruction.’</l>
                        <l n="25">And Balaam rose and went, and he returned
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num024-P256r-L20_trl" n="20"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.025.trl.xml#Num025-P256r-L20_trl" />
                             to his place. And Balak, too, went his way. </l>
                    </ab>
